reviewText: My kids have seen this a few times. From the laughs that I heard seems like they enjoy if every time.I saw it once to see what they enjoyed and it's actually entertaining. Please put your "no high expectations" hat on, and you will enjoy a lot..I tried asking them what they think of the movie and I started a marathon of scenes in the words of a 6 yr old.Never do that again.

reviewText: I had high expectations for this movie and thought my daughter and I would enjoy it, I mean, what is not to like about spies and kids? Well, both of us were deeply disappointed, not only was the pace really slow for a kid's film, the story was poorly conceived and extremely over-the-top at many points of the film, bordering on the ridiculous... Oh, and let's not get started on the poor acting performances across the board... who writes stuff like this? Please don't waste your time with this one, you will be very sorry.
Title: Spy School
